lead_paragraph: Update | 4:44 p.m. Upon further review of the video -- and careful consideration about strengthening the prescription of my eyeglasses -- it appears I mistakenly identified one of the Nano travelers as my friend Gautam Sen. Instead, it was Gautam Raisinghani in the video, and I thank him for alerting me to the misidentification.
snippet: During a road trip across India in a Tata Nano, two travelers chance upon the Bhogilal Vintage Car Collection, which is highlighted by a 1927 Rolls-Royce Phantom I.
